<!DOCTYPE tmc-service-paragraph SYSTEM "../dtd/paragraph-contents.dtd">
<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029758"><name>1GR-FE ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0135343"><name>SFI SYSTEM</name><para id="RM100000000FJG4" category="C"><dtccode>P0724</dtccode><dtcname>Brake Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit High</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000FJG4_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The purpose of this circuit is to prevent the engine from stalling while driving with the lock-up torque converter clutch on when the brakes are suddenly applied.</ptxt><ptxt>When the brake pedal is depressed, the stop light switch sends a signal to the ECM. Then the ECM cancels the operation of the lock-up clutch while braking is in progress.</ptxt><table type="dtc-explan-table" pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.13in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.91in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.91in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.71in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0724</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Brake Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit High</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>The stop light switch remains on even when vehicle is driven in a GO (30 km/h (18.63 mph) or more) and STOP (less than 3 km/h (1.86 mph)) pattern 5 times (2 trip detection logic).</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Short in stop light switch signal circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Stop light switch assembly</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJG4_14" category="03"><name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>This DTC indicates that the stop light switch remains ON. When the stop light switch remains ON during GO and STOP driving, the ECM interprets this as a fault in the stop light switch. Then the MIL illuminatesand the ECM stores the DTC. The vehicle must GO (30 km/h (18.63 mph) or more) and STOP (less than3 km/h (1.86 mph)) 5 times for 2 driving cycles in order for the DTC to be output.</ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJG4_06" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><ptxt>Refer to DTC P0504.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJFD_02"/></mlink></ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJG4_07" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten4><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Using the GTS to read the Data List allows the values or states of switches, sensors, actuators and other items to be read without removing any parts. Reading the Data List information early in troubleshooting is one way to save diagnostic time.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. The ECM records vehicle and driving condition information as freeze frame data the moment a DTC is stored. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can be helpful in determining whether the vehicle was moving or stationary, whether the engine was warmed up or not, whether the air fuel ratio was lean or rich, as well as other data recorded at the time of a malfunction.</ptxt></item></list1></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJG4_13" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000FJG4_13_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>READ VALUE USING GTS (STOP LIGHT SWITCH)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Enter the following menus: Powertrain / Engine and ECT / Data List / Ptrl Throttle / Stop Light Switch.</ptxt><gts-info category="data-list"><title>Powertrain &gt; Engine and ECT &gt; Data List</title><table type="data-list"><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="item-name" args1="117"><ptxt>Stop Light Switch</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><gts-exec function-id="50003"><gts-ecu ecu-id="234"><gts-pid pid-id="117"/></gts-ecu></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">2</app-param><app-param name="category-div">1</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Powertrain</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">234</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Engine and ECT</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param><app-param-unit><app-param name="pid-id">117</app-param><app-param name="data-list-item-name">Stop Light Switch</app-param><app-param name="exception-process-id"/><app-param name="exception-process-div"/></app-param-unit></app-communication></gts-info></test1><test1><ptxt>Read the value displayed on the GTS when the brake pedal is depressed and released.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.62in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.69in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GTS Display</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Measurement Item/Range</ptxt><ptxt>(display)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Normal Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Stop Light Switch</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Stop light switch status: ON or OFF</ptxt></entry><entry><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>ON: Brake pedal depressed</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>OFF: Brake pedal released</ptxt></item></list1></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-1"><actiontitle>CHECK FOR INTERMITTENT PROBLEMS</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJGQ"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-2" childid="RM100000000FJG4_13_0010"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJG4_13_0010" cellposition="2-2"><testtitle>INSPECT STOP LIGHT SWITCH ASSEMBLY</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Inspect the stop light switch assembly.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000G3FJ"/></mlink></ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="4-2" childid="RM100000000FJG4_13_0005"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-3"><actiontitle>REPLACE STOP LIGHT SWITCH ASSEMBLY</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000G3FH"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJG4_13_0005" cellposition="4-2"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (ECM - STOP LIGHT SWITCH ASSEMBLY)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the ECM connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A112585C08" width="3.434793307in" height="4.677165354in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*A</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for LHD</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*B</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for RHD</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Brake Pedal Depressed</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*b</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Brake Pedal Released</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*c</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to ECM)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="voltage"><title>Standard Voltage</title><table><title>for LHD</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center" morerows="1"><ptxt>I84-36 (STP) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Brake pedal depressed</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>11 to 14 V</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Brake pedal released</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>for RHD</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center" morerows="1"><ptxt>A29-36 (STP) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Brake pedal depressed</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>11 to 14 V</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Brake pedal released</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="4-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="5-2"><actiontitle>REPLACE ECM</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJEC"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="4-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="5-3"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp></subpara></para></ttl></section></servcat></pub></tmc-service-paragraph>